01. What is the difference between git reset and git revert. When would you use one over the other?
      git reset: delete a commit we want to delete and reset/delete the commit history from the commit we delete until the final commit
      git revert: delete a commit we want to delete and make it as a commit without affecting the commits we did after that deleted commit

02. What is the difference between git merge and git rebase. When would you use one over the other?
      git merge: merging branches without affecting their previous commit histories, good at a group project.
      git rebase: merging commit histories at all branches to qqmain/master branch and rewrite their previous commit histories as a new commits, good at an individual project.

03. What is the difference between git stash pop and git stash apply. When would you use one over the other?
      git stash pop: deleting the drafted files after using it permanently
      git stash apply: saving back the deleted file to the draft so we can reuse it again whenever we need

04. What kinds of things can you do in interactive mode when rebasing?
      git rebase -i
